Richmont Mines, Inc. (NYSE:RIC) Receives An Update From Brokers


 By Ashley Brown /  in  Stocks /  on  Saturday, 15 Jul 2017 08:04 AM  / 0 Comments




Analysts reviewing Richmont Mines, Inc. have recently updated their recommended buy/sell ratings and price targets on the stock.  			         



Based on their most recently released notes to investors, 2 analysts have a rating of “buy”, 1 analysts “outperform”, 0 analysts “hold”, 0 analysts “underperform” and 0 analysts “sell”.
Ratings and price target breakdown:
 02/01/2017 – Richmont Mines, Inc. was upgraded to “” by analysts at BMO Capital Markets.
 02/01/2017 – Richmont Mines, Inc. was upgraded to “” by analysts at CIBC.
 11/17/2016 – Richmont Mines, Inc. was upgraded to “” by analysts at National Bank Financial.
 11/02/2016 – Richmont Mines, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Scotiabank. They now have a USD 15 price target on the stock.
 11/02/2016 – Richmont Mines, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Desjardins. They now have a USD 14.75 price target on the stock.
 08/10/2016 – Richmont Mines, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at TD Securities. They now have a USD 16.5 price target on the stock.
 08/09/2016 – Richmont Mines, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Canaccord Genuity. They now have a USD 17 price target on the stock.
 06/08/2016 – Richmont Mines, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Pi Financial. They now have a USD 12 price target on the stock.
 04/13/2016 – Richmont Mines, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Paradigm Capital. They now have a USD 10.25 price target on the stock.
 01/19/2016 – Richmont Mines, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Mackie. They now have a USD 6 price target on the stock.
 10/29/2015 – Richmont Mines, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Barclays. They now have a USD 5.5 price target on the stock.
 01/20/2015 – Richmont Mines, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at H.C. Wainwright. They now have a USD 3.75 price target on the stock.
 11/24/2014 – Richmont Mines, Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Zacks. They now have a USD 3.4 price target on the stock.
 01/23/2014 – Macquarie began new coverage on Richmont Mines, Inc. giving the company a “” rating.
Richmont Mines, Inc. has a 50 day moving average of 7.47 and a 200 day moving average of 7.52. The stock’s market capitalization is 490.69M, it has a 52-week low of 5.45 and a 52-week high of 11.66. 
The share price of the company (NYSE:RIC) was up +8.45%, with a high of 7.75 during the day and the volume of Richmont Mines, Inc. shares traded was 403979.  



Richmont Mines Inc. is a mining company. The Company is engaged in mining, exploration and development of mining properties, principally gold. The Company operates gold mines at various sites in Quebec and Ontario. The Company’s segments include Quebec and Ontario. The Company is engaged in producing gold from the Island Gold Mine in Ontario and the Beaufor Mine in Quebec. The Island Gold mine is located 83 kilometers northeast of Wawa, Ontario. It is part of the Island Gold Project, which is divided into nine parts (properties) comprising 219 patented, leased and staked claims covering 7,772 hectares, mainly within the townships of Finan and Jacobson. The Island Gold Project is located in the Michipicoten Greenstone Belt. The Beaufor Mine is located 25 kilometers northeast of Val-d’Or, Quebec. The Camflo mill has rated capacity of 1,200 short tons per day. It is located at Malartic, Quebec. The 7.58 square kilometers Wasamac property is located in the west of Rouyn-Noranda, Quebec.


