Richmont Mines has operated 6 underground gold mines and 1 open-pit gold mine in Canada since 1991. The Corporation currently produces gold from the Island Gold Mine in Ontario and the Beaufor Mine in Quebec, and also operates the Camflo Mill in Quebec. In addition, the Corporation is completing an extensive development program to access a high-grade million ounce deeper resource envelope established directly below its Island Gold Mine, which will reposition the mine into a long-life, higher-production and lower-cost operation capable of generating long term free cash flow and high-quality growth.

























